  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Disciplined Rebalancing</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A supplemental retirement framework &mdash; sell at percentile, rebuy at trend, inside a tax-advantaged account.</p>
  </div>

  <div style="text-align: center;">
    <span class="cs-badge">Phase 3.5 &mdash; coming soon</span>
  </div>

  <div class="cs-content">

    <p class="stub-prose">Disciplined rebalancing is a retirement framework for users with bitcoin held inside a retirement account, where the tax friction that makes most other rebalancing approaches impractical does not apply. The mechanic is bounded by the Power Law channels: when bitcoin&rsquo;s price runs to a high percentile of the trend, sell a defined fraction of the stack; when it returns to or below the trend, rebuy. The discipline is in the triggers &mdash; observable, structurally constrained, and not a function of the user&rsquo;s intuition about market timing.</p>

    <p class="stub-prose">This page is in active development. It will carry its own framing essay, an input surface for percentile triggers and rebuy thresholds, and an output projection that traces the stack across multiple Power Law cycles. The framework requires bitcoin held inside a retirement account, a tolerance for active rebalancing, and at least soft conviction in the Power Law as a guiding model &mdash; which is why it gets its own canvas rather than being folded into the foundational calculator.</p>

    <p class="stub-prose">For the foundational retirement framework &mdash; sell as needed &mdash; return to the primary calculator.</p>

